</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0041-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0041-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>Robinson was using mistrusted as a synonym for suspected.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0041-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0041-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>For an indication of Dinwiddies dealings with Loudoun with regard to the manning of Fort Cumberland, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-04-02-0026-0001&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-04-02-0026-0001-fn-0004#GEWN-02-04-02-0026-0001-fn-0004" class="document">Dinwiddie to GW, 10 Dec. 1756, n.4</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0041-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0041-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>The MS reads to.</p>

</div>
